{
  "texts": [
    "(citing Lochner v. New York, 198 U.S. 45, 76 (1905) (Holmes, J., dissenting))).",
    "59:601 shared community.",
    "113 This participation shapes and validates judgments through a reciprocal relationship between community members and their representatives.",
    "114 It is through this engagement that judgments are not only made but also affirmed and validated by the community.",
    "115 Law, therefore, is not merely a set of rules but a dynamic process of continuous interaction and validation within a political community."
  ]
}